SIMPLE: unhusked
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unhusked
<hw>Un*husked"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>husked</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not husked; having
the husk on.</def> <-- #2. "husked" here means having the husk removed.
This word has opposite meanings. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> + <ets>husk</ets>,
n.]</ety> <def>Having the husk removed; without husk.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uni-</ent>⟦br⟧
